{"id":"canary-deep-runeward-runeward-L4-s108302-0000","meta":{"family":"runeward","kind":"atom","level":4,"stratum":"deep"},"prompt_sha256":"dfedae9f81e1011694538814b8222d847cd38100a31c7abd73de4625b6a48a97","n_prompt_tokens":279,"prompt_channel":"thinking","prompt_logprobs":null,"outputs":[{"sample_index":0,"stage1_parent_seed":922876560,"seed_stage1":922876560,"seed_stage2":1781498603,"text":"Let me find the charge of the quen ward. I'll translate the bindings into equations and check whether they all hold together.\n\nLet Q, U, A, D, B denote the charges of the quen, ule, ando, drell, brasp wards. Each is an integer from 1 to 9.\n\nBinding 1: U + B = 11.\nBinding 2: Q = A + 1.\nBinding 3: U = D + 2.\nBinding 4: U = A + 2.\nBinding 5: Q ≠ B.\nBinding 6: A + D = 10.\nBinding 7: Q ≠ D.\nBinding 8: U = Q + 1.\nBinding 9: D > B.\n\nFirst, bindings 3 and 4 both describe U. From them, D + 2 = A + 2, so D = A.\nBut binding 6 says A + D = 10, and if D = A then 2A = 10, so A = 5 and D = 5.\nNow binding 3 gives U = 5 + 2 = 7.\n</think>\n\nANSWER: quen<|im_end|>\n","token_ids":[9764,728,1423,279,6545,314,279,172445,24839,13,353,3172,14260,279,34519,1083,36655,321,1716,3315,781,660,3222,3658,13,271,9764,1167,11,533,11,357,11,414,11,417,75389,279,9892,314,279,172445,11,560,273,11,321,78,11,293,15806,11,1363,12980,74512,13,8618,369,449,7308,494,220,16,310,220,24,13,271,14621,220,16,25,533,478,417,283,220,16,16,13,198,14621,220,17,25,1167,283,357,478,220,16,13,198,14621,220,18,25,533,283,414,478,220,17,13,198,14621,220,19,25,533,283,357,478,220,17,13,198,14621,220,20,25,1167,91050,417,13,198,14621,220,21,25,357,478,414,283,220,16,15,13,198,14621,220,22,25,1167,91050,414,13,198,14621,220,23,25,533,283,1167,478,220,16,13,198,14621,220,24,25,414,835,417,13,271,5170,11,34519,220,18,321,220,19,2107,7276,533,13,5369,1070,11,414,478,220,17,283,357,478,220,17,11,748,414,283,357,13,198,3850,10649,220,21,2640,357,478,414,283,220,16,15,11,321,413,414,283,357,1179,220,17,32,283,220,16,15,11,